A total of 2,322 delegates drawn from the 774 local governments across Nigeria have commenced voting at the APC Special Convention at the Eagle Square, Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja. With three delegates drawn from each of the 774 local governments, the All Progressives Congress (APC), will seek to find a flag-bearer for the ruling party ahead of the 2023 presidential election, with Vice President Yemi Osinbajo and former Lagos State Governor Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, seen as the leading contenders to emerge a winner when the votes are counted later today. In the highlight of the three-day event which kicked off on Monday, six aspirants â€“ immediate past Minister of the Niger Delta, Godswill Akpabio, Senator Ibikunle Amosun, Ekiti State Governor Kayode Fayemi, Jigawa State Governor Muhammad Badaru, former Speaker of the House of Assembly Dimeji Bankole, Senator Ajayi Boroffice and the only female among the 23 aspirants, Barrister Uju Ohanenye, all dropped their presidential ambition for Asiwaju Tinubu. In a similar manner, the youngest of the aspirants, Nicholas Felix, stepped down for Vice President Osinbajo.